IncidentSuppNarrative.NarrativeText: Attachments -NCMEC Cybertips # 155448834 -Neustar information for the phone number -Preservation Letter for Synchronoss Technologies Narrative On March 17, 2023, the Maryland State Police Computer Crimes Section /Maryland Internet Crimes Against Children Task Force received NCMEC CyberTip # 155448834. The CyberTip, generated by Synchronoss Technologies, indicated that a subject uploaded child pornography to the internet. The CyberTip were assigned to TFC Burnett for investigation. The CyberTip provided the following information pertaining to the suspect: Phone: 4434040688 TFC Burnett reviewed this CyberTip and observed it to contain one reported video file that constitutes child pornography as it is defined under Maryland law. The file is described below: Filename #1: db29f3d37ca14ed5864b1e10630b1f03_07b1105e6bbbde97e904c6ca497 5ceaf151a1d2e6c848faa2ed6ada154134d58 Description: This file is a one minute and eighteen-second colored video of a Caucasian female child wearing a white tank top with a flower/butterfly design, and she is nude from the waist down. The child is laying on a bed while an adult male vaginally penetrates her exposed vagina. Based on the size and physical characteristics, the child appears to be 12-15 years of age. TFC Burnett conducted a query of the phone number through an open-source database. The phone number (443-404-0688) is registered to a Jaime Knisely through Verizon and geo-locates to the area of Solomons, MD. TFC Burnettauthored a subpoena for Verizon (phone number), it was sent to the Howard County States Attorneys Office. A preservation letter was sent to Synchronoss Technologies to preserve the suspects account. Case Status OPEN / PENDING ADDITIONAL INVESTIGATION

Attachments: -Signed Verizon subpoena -Signed Synchronoss Technologies search warrant -Verizon subscriber information -Verizon device information -Signed Maryland State Police Search Warrant Report and Return (Form 98) for Synchronoss Technologies --Signed Maryland State Police Evidence Inventory (Form 98A) for Synchronoss Technologies Narrative: On 3/27/2023, I received the signed Verizon subpoena from the States Attorneys Office. On 3/29/2023, I submitted the signed Verizon subpoena through email. On 4/7/2023, I authored a search warrant for the suspects Synchronoss Technologies account and it was signed by the Honorable Judge Chandlee with the Calvert County Circuit Court. The signed search warrant was submitted. On 4/10/2023, I received the Synchronoss Technologies search warrant return with the folders labeled Call, mms, and sms which contained numerous folders that were mainly messages coming in and going out along with a folder called VZMOBILE with 435 items of adult pornography and miscellaneous images. Some of those images contained identifiable information for the suspect. The below information is what was found, there was no child pornography located within the account. -Maryland Identification Card: James Ryan Knisely (W/M, DOB: 7/17/1982), located at 2199 Stoney Valley Drive, Manchester, MD -Social Security Card: 216-08-6436 On 4/12/2023, I received the Verizon subpoena return with the below information: Subscriber: Renee Osborn Phone: 443-404-0688 Home phone: 443-904-4852 Address: 37 Governors Gate Ln, Linthicum, MD Device Name: Samsung Galaxy S23 IMEI:355552519269980 It appears that Renee Osborn is in a relationship with James through Facebook since 2/10/2023. Based on the lack of child pornography in James account, a knock and talk will be conducted. On 4/18/2023, the Honorable Judge Chandlee signed the Maryland State Police Search Warrant Report and Return (Form 98) and theMaryland State Police Evidence Inventory (Form 98A) for the Synchronoss Technologies search warrant. Case open, investigation ongoing.

LIST OF EXHIBITS MSP Form 53 NARRATIVE On 4/19/2023, at approximately 1430 hours, Cpl. Heid, of the Maryland State Police Child Recovery Unit, and TFC Mueller, of the Maryland State Police Computer Crimes Unit, responded to37 Governors Gate Lane Linthicum Heights, MD 21090 to conduct a knock and talk. Investigators eventually made contact with James Knisely, the suspect of the investigation. TFC Mueller explained the nature of the investigation to Knisely. Knisely stated he used to have the Kik application on his cell phone, but deleted it once he kept getting sent child pornography. Knisely signed a MSP Form 53 and consented to a search of his phone, which TFC Mueller conducted. TFC Mueller did not observe any child pornography. Knisley was provided with an internet safety discussion and was grateful for police services. Case Closed, by exception.
